Reasoning: The paper describes a software package for network inference and analysis of node dynamics using information theory. This falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) in computer science. The use of machine learning techniques such as transfer entropy and mutual information suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The analysis of node dynamics may also fall under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the use of parallel computing engines suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SI).
